HEADWORD: hippeastrum
<hw>hippeastrum</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>An amaryllis of tropical America
(<spn>Hippeastrum puniceum</spn>) often cultivated as a houseplant for
its showy white to red flowers.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> <spn>Hippeastrum puniceum</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
